But it is not easy to see why continuous motion as a whole should not be omitted, if that modification of it which admits periods of rest at fixed pitches is rejected, inasmuch as the latter is far more musical in its nature than the former. Without steadiness in the piteh it would be almost impossible to gain an idea of musical interval, and all musicis based on interval, or the relation which subsiste between musical notes.
